package main

// A variadic function returning a view into its variadic parameter. The
// variadic pack is a caller-frame-synthesized slice whose lifetime is the
// call, not a normal borrowed parameter, and the positional
// param-index→argument mapping breaks down for the packed args. v1 rejects
// a returned alias of a variadic parameter outright (never recorded).
fn first(args ...any) any[] {
	return args[0:1]
}

fn main() {}
